  "playingCareerSummary": "'The Wall' — one of India's greatest Test batters and former India captain: 164 Tests (13,288 runs at 52.31), 344 ODIs (10,889 runs). Played for Royal Challengers Bangalore (2008-2010) and Rajasthan Royals (2011-2013) in the IPL, captaining RR in 2012 and 2013.",
  "bio": "Rajasthan Royals head coach for IPL 2025, reuniting with the franchise where he had captained in 2012-2013 and mentored in 2014-2015. Took charge after Kumar Sangakkara's four-year tenure but RR had a poor 2025 campaign, finishing 9th. Left after a single season and Sangakkara returned for 2026. Best known for his transformative tenure as India national team head coach (2021-2024), winning the 2024 T20 World Cup.",
